dback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hby1665702835478.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hby1665702835478.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hby1665702835478.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hby1665702835478\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define/Edit Print Job Model\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Define a new print job model, or edit an existing model.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hby1665702835478__section_w126ab1b7b1_w127ab1b7_w128ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hby1665702835478__section_w129ab1b7b3_w130ab1b7_w131ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1159182e60\">\n                       \n Fields\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hby1665702835478__li_d4442e1_d4443e1_d4444e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"upo1665702675641.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upo1665702675641.html\" title=\"Name of the print job model.\">Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hby1665702835478__li_d4445e1_d4446e1_d4447e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xmq1665702675709.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xmq1665702675709.html\" title=\"Name of the device translation table to use for this print job model.\">Device Type</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hby1665702835478__li_d4448e1_d4449e1_d4450e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ymx1665702675781.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ymx1665702675781.html\" title=\"The Print Queue specifies the destination of the printed output.\">Print Queue</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hby1665702835478__li_d4451e1_d4452e1_d4453e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xhc1665702675851.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xhc1665702675851.html\" title=\"Print options provide additional parameters for the operating system print command, or the command specified in Print Queue.\">Print Options</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hby1665702835478__li_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ozu1665702675920.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ozu1665702675920.html\" title=\"A device mode is a collection of predefined page formatting attributes for a device translation table. It controls the number of columns and lines, character width, line depth, and page orientation. Each printer device translation table has its own set of modes.\">Device Mode</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hby1665702835478__li_d4457e1_d4458e1_d4459e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lwg1665702675989.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lwg1665702675989.html\" title=\"Margins of the printed output are expressed in terms of lines and characters.\">Margins</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hby1665702835478__li_d4460e1_d4461e1_d4462e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print using colors</span>—prints the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rwc1665702587483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rwc1665702587483.html\" title=\"Color to use as the background of the object.\">Background Color (BackColor)</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rbp1665702587714.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rbp1665702587714.html\" title=\"Color to use as the foreground (usually the text color).\">Foreground Color (ForeColor)</a> of a widget, if they are defined. Otherwise, the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print black on white</span> option is used.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hby1665702835478__section_w132ab1b7b5_w133ab1b7_w134ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1159182e159\">\n                       \n How to\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hby1665702835478__p_d9629e1_d9630e1_d9631e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nbh1665702675570.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nbh1665702675570.html\" title=\"You must define a print job model before you can print data from Form components.\">Define a Print Job Model</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/guw1665702607063.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Print Job Models</a><p>A print job model is a named collection of printer attributes that determine how and where Uniface forms or reports are printed, including details of the device type, margins, and so on. A print job model must be available before you can print.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rch1665702606837.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Printing Character Sets</a><p>To print, choose the device translation table that is specific for the character set.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528137\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528137\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define/Edit Print Job Model Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define/Edit Print Job Model Define a new print job model, or edit an existing model. Fields Name Device Type Print Queue Print Options Device Mode Margins Print using colors —prints the Background Color (BackColor) and Foreground Color (ForeColor) of a widget, if they are defined. Otherwise, the Print black on white option is used. How to Define a Print Job Model Related Links Print Job Models A print job model is a named collection of printer attributes that determine how and where Uniface forms or reports are printed, including details of the device type, margins, and so on. A print job model must be available before you can print. Printing Character Sets To print, choose the device translation table that is specific for the character set. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}